President Barack Obama has announced his intention to nominate Thomas M. Beck for the position of Board Member at the National Mediation Board. Beck currently serves as a Member of the Federal Labor Relations Authority and has handled over 400 labor disputes in that role. He was previously the Chairman of the FLRA and has extensive experience in private law practice, including appearing in federal and state courts, arguing in federal appellate courts, representing clients before regulatory agencies, and handling labor arbitrations. Beck has also taught courses on Constitutional separation of powers and the federal legislative process at George Mason University School of Law. He holds undergraduate and law degrees from the University of Virginia.